The Boston Beer Company, Inc. Reports Consolidated Unaudited Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended April 1, 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for 2017
Apr 26 17
The Boston Beer Company, Inc. reported consolidated unaudited earnings results for the first quarter ended April 1, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported revenue was $172,437,000 against $202,009,000 reported last year. Operating income was $4,028,000 against $11,237,000 reported last year. Income before income tax provision was $4,040,000 against $11,041,000 reported last year. Net income $5,711,000 or $0.45 per diluted per share against $7,032,000 or $0.53 diluted reported last year. Net cash used in operating activities was $5,040,000 against net cash provided by operating activities was $9,267,000 reported last year. Purchases of property, plant and equipment was $6,981,000 against $13,011,000 reported last year. Net revenue decrease was mainly due to decline in shipments of 15%, partially offset by price increases.

Full-year 2017 the company currently projects full year 2017 earnings per diluted share to be between $4.20 and $6.20, reflecting the uncertain volume outlook. Gross margin of between 51% and 52%, increasing during the year due to progress on the cost saving initiatives. Effective tax rate of approximately 37%, excluding the impact of ASU 2016-09. Estimated capital spending of between $30 million and $50 million, most of which relates to continued investments in the Company’s breweries.


The Boston Beer Company, Inc., Annual General Meeting, May 18, 2017
Apr 7 17
The Boston Beer Company, Inc., Annual General Meeting, May 18, 2017, at 09:00 US Eastern Standard Time. Location: Samuel Adams Brewery 30 Germania Street Boston Massachusetts United States Agenda: The Class A Stockholders to consider for the election of 3 Class A Directors, each to serve for a term of 1 year; to conduct an advisory vote to approve the compensation of Named Executive Officers; to conduct an advisory vote on the frequency of holding future advisory votes on the compensation of Named Executive Officers; and to consider and act upon any other business that may properly come before the meeting; The Class B Stockholders to consider for the election of 5 Class B Directors, each to serve for a term of 1 year; to ratify the selection of Deloitte & Touche LLP as independent registered public accounting firm for Fiscal Year 2017; and to consider and act upon any other business that may properly come before the meeting.


